## ✅ PHASE 4 — GitHub Collaborator Management (COMPLETE)

> **This is the new core enterprise feature replacing the old Teams/Orgs system.**  
> **Real GitHub collaboration data via GitHub API — no fake internal system.**

### What We're Building

```
User connects a repo
  ↓
CodeLens shows current GitHub collaborators
  ↓
User can:
  ├── Add new collaborator (by GitHub username)
  ├── Remove existing collaborator
  ├── Change permission level (pull / push / admin)
  └── See per-collaborator activity stats
        ├── PRs opened
        ├── Files changed (which files)
        ├── Lines added / deleted
        └── Last active
```

---

### Step 4.1 — GitHub Collaborator API Module

**File:** [module/collaborator/lib/github-collaborators.ts](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/lib/github-collaborators.ts)

Functions to build using **Octokit REST API**:

| Function                                                     | GitHub API                                                      | What it does                                     |
| ------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| [listCollaborators(token, owner, repo)](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/lib/github-collaborators.ts#28-57)                      | `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/collaborators`                       | List all collaborators with permissions          |
| [addCollaborator(token, owner, repo, username, permission)](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/lib/github-collaborators.ts#60-83)  | `PUT /repos/{owner}/{repo}/collaborators/{username}`            | Add collaborator (sends invite or adds directly) |
| [removeCollaborator(token, owner, repo, username)](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/actions/index.ts#160-168)           | `DELETE /repos/{owner}/{repo}/collaborators/{username}`         | Remove collaborator access                       |
| `updatePermission(token, owner, repo, username, permission)` | `PUT /repos/{owner}/{repo}/collaborators/{username}`            | Change permission level                          |
| `getCollaboratorPermission(token, owner, repo, username)`    | `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/collaborators/{username}/permission` | Get specific permission                          |
| [listPendingInvitations(token, owner, repo)](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/lib/github-collaborators.ts#122-145)                 | `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/invitations`                         | See pending (not-yet-accepted) invites           |
| [cancelInvitation(token, owner, repo, invitationId)](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/actions/index.ts#186-194)         | `DELETE /repos/{owner}/{repo}/invitations/{invitationId}`       | Cancel an invite                                 |

**Permission levels:**

- `pull` — Read only
- `push` — Read + Write
- `maintain` — No destructive actions
- `admin` — Full control
- `triage` — Can manage issues/PRs but not code

**Schema addition needed:**

```prisma
// No new DB table needed!
// Collaborator data comes LIVE from GitHub API every time.
// Only cache: per-collaborator activity stats (derived from existing FileChange + ReviewDetail)
```

---

### Step 4.2 — Collaborator Actions (Server Actions)

**File:** [module/collaborator/actions/index.ts](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/actions/index.ts)

```typescript
// Actions to create:
getCollaborators(repoId); // Fetch from GitHub API + merge local activity stats
addCollaborator(repoId, username, permission); // GitHub API + log action
removeCollaborator(repoId, username); // GitHub API + log action
updateCollaboratorPermission(repoId, username, permission); // GitHub API
getPendingInvites(repoId); // GitHub API — list pending invites
cancelPendingInvite(repoId, invitationId); // GitHub API
getCollaboratorActivity(repoId, githubUsername); // From local DB (FileChange + ReviewDetail)
```

**Each collaborator card will show:**

- GitHub avatar + username + display name
- Current permission badge (pull/push/admin in color)
- **PRs authored** (count from `ReviewDetail.prAuthor`)
- **Files changed** (count from `FileChange.changedBy`)
- **Total lines added/deleted** (sum from `FileChange`)
- **Last activity date**
- Actions: Change Permission / Remove

---

### Step 4.3 — Developer Activity Per File (Key Feature)

**The main insight:** Which developer touched which files and how much?

Data already exists in `FileChange` table (has `changedBy` = GitHub username, `filePath`, `linesAdded`, `linesDeleted`).

New query to add in [module/collaborator/actions/index.ts](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/collaborator/actions/index.ts):

```typescript
// Per developer → which files they changed and how many times
getDeveloperFileActivity(repoId, githubUsername);
// Returns:
// [
//   { filePath: "src/api/auth.ts", timesChanged: 5, linesAdded: 120, linesDeleted: 45 },
//   { filePath: "src/utils/parse.ts", timesChanged: 3, linesAdded: 32, linesDeleted: 10 },
// ]

// Per file → which developers touched it
getFileDeveloperActivity(repoId, filePath);
// Returns:
// [
//   { developer: "john_dev", timesChanged: 5, linesAdded: 120 },
//   { developer: "jane_dev", timesChanged: 2, linesAdded: 30 },
// ]
```

