## ✅ PHASE 9 — Real Engineering Analytics (COMPLETE — zero cron, zero new models)

> 📄 Original spec: [diff/05-feature-engineering-analytics.md](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/diff/05-feature-engineering-analytics.md)  
> **What we built:** On-demand analytics — all data from existing DB tables + AI review text parsing. No background jobs, no cron, no new Prisma models, no LLM token usage.

### Approach: Parse Risk from Stored Review Text

The AI review prompt (Phase 8) already produces structured `## Risk: X/100` output with severity-tagged issues.
Instead of separate scoring models/cron, we **parse this at query time** via `review-parser.ts`.

### Backend — Review Parser ✅

**File:** [module/analytics/lib/review-parser.ts](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/analytics/lib/review-parser.ts)

- [x] `parseReviewText(reviewText)` → `ParsedReview` (riskScore, riskReason, issues[], summary, criticalCount, warningCount, suggestionCount)
- [x] `parseReviewsBatch(reviews)` — batch parser for arrays
- [x] `getRiskLevel(score)` → `{label, color, bg}` (critical/high/medium/low)
- [x] Regex-based extraction: `## Risk: X/100 — reason`, `- **file:line** — description`, code fix blocks
- [x] Severity detection: critical, warning, suggestion, info — from emoji or text
- [x] Summary extraction from `## Summary` section

### Backend — New Server Actions ✅

**File:** [module/analytics/actions/index.ts](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/module/analytics/actions/index.ts)

| Function | What it does |
|---|---|
| `getEnhancedOverview()` | Global stats + risk metrics (avg risk, critical count, total issues) |
| `getRiskAnalytics(days)` | Weekly risk trend, risk distribution pie, per-repo risk, top issues |
| `getFileHotspots(repoId?, limit)` | File change aggregation + cross-referenced issues + GitHub file links |
| `getDeveloperActivity(repoId?)` | PR count, files, lines per developer with avatar |
| `getRepoBreakdown()` | Per-repo stats: reviews, risk, issues, indexing status, GitHub link |
| `getReviewTimeline(days)` | Daily review volume (completed vs failed) for area charts |
| `getHighRiskReviews(limit)` | Top riskiest PRs with parsed risk score, issues, and PR link |

### Frontend — 5-Tab Analytics Dashboard ✅

**File:** [app/dashboard/analytics/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/app/dashboard/analytics/page.tsx)

**Layout:**
```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Engineering Analytics                                    │
├──────── 8 stat cards (reviews, repos, 30d, 7d, files,   │
│         issues, avg risk, gen time)                        │
├──────── Risk summary bar (critical + high count)          │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [Overview] [Risk Analytics] [File Hotspots]              │
│  [Developers] [Performance]                               │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                          │
│  Tab 1 — Overview:                                       │
│    PRs per user (bar) + Code churn (area)                │
│    Review activity timeline (stacked area, 90d)          │
│    Repository health table (risk badges, indexing)       │
│                                                          │
│  Tab 2 — Risk Analytics:                                 │
│    Risk trend (line, weekly avg) + Distribution (pie)    │
│    Risk by repository (horizontal bar, color-coded)      │
│    Highest risk PRs table (score, issues, reason, link)  │
│    Top issues found by AI (severity-coded cards)         │
│                                                          │
│  Tab 3 — File Hotspots:                                  │
│    Hotspot chart (stacked bar: added/deleted)            │
│    Detailed file table (changes, churn, issues, GitHub)  │
│    Files per repository (grouped bar)                    │
│                                                          │
│  Tab 4 — Developers:                                     │
│    Contributions bar + Code volume bar                   │
│    Developer activity table (avatar, PRs, files, churn)  │
│                                                          │
│  Tab 5 — Performance:                                    │
│    AI usage per member (bar) + Gen time trend (line)     │
│    Review status distribution (pie) + Daily volume (area)│
│    Most modified files table                             │
│                                                          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| No new DB models | Review text already contains risk + issues — parse don't duplicate |
| No cron / background jobs | On-demand Prisma queries are fast enough for dashboard use |
| No LLM token usage | All analytics from existing DB data + regex parsing |
| 5 tabs vs single scroll | Better UX, lazy-loaded per tab via React Query |
| GitHub file links | Direct `https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/blob/main/{path}` links |
| RiskBadge component | Consistent risk rendering across all tables |
| Stacked area charts | Show completed vs failed reviews over time |

