## ✅ PHASE 10 — Self-Improving Feedback Loop (COMPLETE)

> 📄 Full spec: [diff/03-feature-self-improving-feedback-loop.md](file:///c:/Users/prana/OneDrive/Desktop/codelensai/diff/03-feature-self-improving-feedback-loop.md)

- [x] `ReviewFeedback` + `FeedbackAggregation` Prisma models — pushed to Neon
- [x] 👍👎❌💡 feedback buttons on every review card (`components/feedback-widget.tsx`)
- [x] Feedback persists on refresh — `getReviews()` includes user's existing reaction, hydrated via `initialReaction` prop
- [x] Filled icon state when selected (lucide `fill="currentColor"`)
- [x] `submitFeedback()` server action with input sanitization (prompt-injection safe)
- [x] `getFeedbackForReview()` server action — returns section→reaction map
- [x] `getFeedbackPromptContext()` — reads aggregated hints, sanitizes before prompt injection, capped at 5 hints
- [x] `groupByCategory()` + `generatePromptHints()` — accuracy-based hint generation (`module/feedback/lib/aggregation.ts`)
- [x] `aggregateFeedback` Inngest cron — every 6 hours, upserts `FeedbackAggregation` per repo per category
- [x] Review pipeline Step 3: `fetch-feedback-context` — injects team hints into `buildReviewPrompt()`
- [x] `buildReviewPrompt()` updated with optional `feedbackContext` param — zero token cost until 3+ feedback entries exist

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| No LLM calls in feedback system | 100% DB + TypeScript logic — zero Gemini token cost |
| Sanitize hints before prompt injection | Strip `<>{}` + length cap — prevents prompt injection from user comments |
| Min 3 samples before hints activate | Avoids bad signal from single reactions |
| `@@unique([reviewId, userId, section])` | One reaction per user per section — prevents ballot stuffing |
| Feedback visible on refresh | `getReviews()` includes feedback relation filtered to current user |

